title: José Güity
text:
José César Güity Vuelto (born 19 May 1985) is a <a href="Honduras">Honduran</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> player.
Club career.
Nicknamed "Baba", Güity started his career at <a href="C.D.%20Marath%C3%B3n">Marathón</a> and joined Chinese side <a href="Shanghai%20Shenhua%20F.C.">Shanghai Shenhua</a> for a short spell after the Beijing Olympics. After he returned to Honduras to play for <a href="C.D.S.%20Vida">Vida</a>, he again moved abroad in summer 2009 to play for Costa Rican side <a href="C.S.%20Herediano">Herediano</a>, and made his debut in July 2009, immediately scoring the winning goal against <a href="L.D.%20Alajuelense">L.D. Alajuelense</a>. However, he already left them in August 2009 to make his debut for Guatemalan outfit <a href="Pe%C3%B1arol%20La%20Mesilla">Peñarol La Mesilla</a> in October 2009.
Güity joined Guatemalans <a href="C.D.%20Jalapa">Jalapa</a> for the 2010 Apertura championship. In July 2011 he went on trial to Salvadoran giants Alianza but he ended up in the Honduran second division with <a href="Parrillas%20One">Parrillas One</a>. He joined <a href="C.D.%20Real%20Sociedad">Real Sociedad</a> for the 2012 Clausura.
International career.
Güity played three games at the <a href="2005%20FIFA%20World%20Youth%20Championship">2005 FIFA World Youth Championship</a> in the Netherlands.
He was also part of the U-23 <a href="Honduras%20national%20football%20team">Honduras national football team</a> that won the <a href="2008%20CONCACAF%20Men%27s%20Pre-Olympic%20Tournament">2008 CONCACAF Men's Pre-Olympic Tournament</a> and qualified to the <a href="2008%20Summer%20Olympics">2008 Summer Olympics</a>.
